-- Taiwan Equity Movers: Ichia Technologies, Silitech, Ta Chong
-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 2012-05-30T06:56:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-30/taiwan-equity-movers-htc-corp-ichia-technologies-silitech.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei trading.  The Taiex Index dropped 1.1 percent to 7,261.80, following
a 2.9 percent rally yesterday. The gauge has fallen 3.2 percent
in May, poised for the third straight monthly drop.  Research In Motion (RIMM)  Ltd.-related suppliers:  Ichia
Technologies Inc. (2402)  (2402 TT) lost 2.2 percent to NT$15.7.
 Silitech Technology Corp. (3311)  (3311 TT) dropped 0.3 percent to
NT$68.9.  Unitech Printed Circuit Board Corp. (2367)  (2367 TT) declined
0.9 percent to NT$11.2. Research In Motion, reeling from
sluggish BlackBerry sales, forecast a surprise operating loss
for the first quarter and hired banks to advise on strategic
options.  Ta Chong Bank Ltd. (2847)  (2847 TT) lost 5 percent to NT$9.18,
taking a four-day slump to 22 percent. The company said on May
25 Yuanta Financial Holding Co. and Fubon Financial Holding Co.
have stopped merger-related assessments and procedures.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
